-Introduce basics of programming (slide deck)
--What is a coding language
--How does the computer read code
--Very brief description of binary (on/off, zeroes and ones, they represent whether electricity is going through or not)
--Bring up that computers count from 0 (for most languages & python included)

-Teaching (visual demonstration + pictures)
--How to import libraries
--What are variables
--Introduce variable naming standards (snake case for python, but mention other types aswell)
--simple syntax (keeping variable names consistent)
--How to control the buzzer (mention that this is done through functions, which will be taught later)
--How to write comments, and the importance of writing comments

-Introduce the lesson's project
--What is morse code
--Make it share a simple "HI" or "HEY" as a demonstration, then let students make their own messages
--During this lesson, students will also learn that computers are very fast, and will need to add delays between lines

--Final outcome of this lesson will be to make the raspbot share a message through morse code